Key Match Events: Anthony Edwards scored the go-ahead basket with a floating jump shot that put Minnesota on top 117-116 with 25.7 seconds to go.
Gobert added a pair of free throws with 10.1 seconds left to increase the lead to three.
Jokic fired a 3-point attempt from the right corner that missed in the waning seconds.
Minnesota trailed by 10 points in the fourth quarter before closing the game on a 17-4 run to secure the victory.
